    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nFiles opened via `--remote` are interpreted as relative to neovim `cwd`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n/my_app -> neovim cwd\r\n/my_app/client -> cwd of shell executing --remote\r\n/my_app/...\r\n```\r\nFiles opened via `--remote`in `/my_app/client`, e.g. by a linter running in this subdirectory, are resolved with the wrong directory (`/my_app`).\r\n\r\nFiles opened via `--remote` should be interpreted with a absolute path. `neovim-remote` supports this since 2016: https://github.com/mhinz/neovim-remote/pull/2",
